- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on part-of-speech induction.
- cs.LG (Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a refined model and learning objective to control model capacity.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper addresses the problem of unsupervised learning of grammatical categories, which is a common task in AI.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper proposes an efficient learning algorithm, which may involve neural networks or evolutionary algorithms.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper may involve the development of new algorithms or data structures to address the problem of part-of-speech induction.
